JOHANNESBURG - Metrorail says train services between Vereeniging and Johannesburg will resume on Tuesday after a month-long suspension.The services were shut down after violent service delivery protests at Nancefield station in Soweto.READ - Train services suspended, shops closed in Kliptown protestsProtesters barricaded roads with rocks and burning tyres, making the station inaccessible.Two people died during the unrest.Metrorail says the first phase to restore services has been successfully implemented.Some taxi routes in Soweto were recently suspended following taxi-related violence in the area that has already led to the death of 5 people. WATCH - Grieving mother pleads for an end to Soweto taxi violence... eNCA